# How to deploy Ceph cluster

1. Prepare /dev/vdb which size is more than 5GiB, in the test machine. If you want to change the device name, please modify the `vdb` with other name in the cluster-sat.yaml.

1. Prepare the cluster created by topolvm(HEAD is 5b451eb64f34816a726903062812726a0fcd4083) e2e test.

1. Apply the following resources of Rook/Ceph.

```console
$ kubectl apply -f common.yaml
$ kubectl apply -f operator-with-csi.yaml
$ kubectl apply -f cluster-sat.yaml
```

1. (it can skip) Confirmed that raw block volume feature works fine

```console
$ kubectl apply -f raw-block-volume-pod-test.yaml
kubectl exec -it raw-block-volume-pod-test -- bash
# ls -l /dev/block
brw-rw-rw- 1 root root 253, 9 Aug 29 07:40 /dev/block
# exit
$ kubectl delete pod raw-block-volume-pod-test
```
